1
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:29,112
<font color="#FFFFFF">Send a rider tonight
and he'll be back by morning.</font>

2
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:32,352
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why don't they let
us dry ourselves and get warm?</font>

3
00:01:33,159 --> 00:01:35,436
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I stay like this,
I will rust.</font>

4
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,795
<font color="#FFFFFF">What kind of fellow
is this Jarl Borg?</font>

5
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,912
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is no way to treat
guests, whoever they are.</font>

6
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">Especially if they've been
traveling for days on end.</font>

7
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:05,920
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you the emissaries
from King Horik?</font>

8
00:02:07,879 --> 00:02:09,677
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I can tell you at once,
you're wasting your time.</font>

9
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:13,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's my land, and I
want it returned to me.</font>

10
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:14,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's all I have to say.</font>

11
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,272
<font color="#FFFFFF">He wants to make peace with you</font>

12
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:21,149
<font color="#FFFFFF">and come to some
kind of agreement.</font>

13
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then tell him if he leaves
my land, we can have peace.</font>

14
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,239
<font color="#FFFFFF">But not before.</font>

15
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:34,311
<font color="#FFFFFF">How can you make
peace, Jarl Borg,</font>

16
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,550
<font color="#FFFFFF">if you insist on
humiliating him?</font>

17
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,716
<font color="#FFFFFF">If I invade and defeat him,</font>

18
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,554
<font color="#FFFFFF">will he not be
even more humiliated?</font>

19
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:42,954
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not if he fights well.</font>

20
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,795
<font color="#FFFFFF">In any case,</font>

21
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:50,031
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am sure that
he would relish a fight.</font>

22
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,235
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's your name?</font>

23
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ragnar Lothbrok.</font>

24
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:12,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are Ragnar Lothbrok,</font>

25
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,633
<font color="#FFFFFF">the one who sailed west?</font>

26
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:18,352
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am surprised that
you've heard about that.</font>

27
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">How are you surprised?</font>

28
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,872
<font color="#FFFFFF">Everyone has heard
of your exploits.</font>

29
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,836
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why have we not offered our
guests dry clothes and food?</font>

30
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:39,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">Treat these folk well.</font>

31
00:03:39,199 --> 00:03:42,795
<font color="#FFFFFF">Give them ale,
let them dry out, feed them.</font>

32
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:46,158
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tomorrow, you and I will
talk again, Ragnar Lothbrok.</font>

33
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,516
<font color="#FFFFFF">You haven't eaten in three days.</font>

34
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:29,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">You see?</font>

35
00:04:33,199 --> 00:04:34,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have fears.</font>

36
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go to the Seer,</font>

37
00:04:40,879 --> 00:04:43,348
<font color="#FFFFFF">ask if your fears
will come true.</font>

38
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:45,829
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's sometimes better
not to know one's fate.</font>

39
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:50,557
<font color="#FFFFFF">I take it,
from what you said yesterday,</font>

40
00:04:50,639 --> 00:04:52,278
<font color="#FFFFFF">that King Horik is
prepared to compromise</font>

41
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:55,750
<font color="#FFFFFF">and offer some deal
regarding those lands of mine,</font>

42
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,274
<font color="#FFFFFF">which he still occupies?</font>

43
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:58,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">He is prepared to pay you</font>

44
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">to renounce your illegal claims</font>

45
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">of his lands.</font>

46
00:05:02,959 --> 00:05:04,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">You disappoint me now,
Ragnar Lothbrok.</font>

47
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,920
<font color="#FFFFFF">I thought you'd come here
with a serious purpose.</font>

48
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you would just
name your price.</font>

49
00:05:08,439 --> 00:05:09,714
<font color="#FFFFFF">The land is priceless.</font>

50
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:13,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which is why King Horik
wants to keep it for himself.</font>

51
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,396
<font color="#FFFFFF">Every piece of land has a
price, just like every human.</font>

52
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,153
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, you don't understand.</font>

53
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,276
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is not a small plot of land</font>

54
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:23,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">on which you grow
turnips and onions.</font>

55
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're talking about
a vast swathe of land,</font>

56
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:29,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">and on this land, in the earth, are
minerals, things of great value.</font>

57
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:32,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why else would I
assert my claim?</font>

58
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:34,636
<font color="#FFFFFF">King Horik resists your claim,</font>

59
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,598
<font color="#FFFFFF">but still, in good faith,</font>

60
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,672
<font color="#FFFFFF">he is willing to
settle with you.</font>

61
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:42,149
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you will name
a reasonable price.</font>

62
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:47,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">At the moment,
my price is King Horik's head.</font>

63
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:51,634
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, then,</font>

64
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,033
<font color="#FFFFFF">it seems I am done.</font>

65
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,757
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hold on, please, sit
down, sit down.</font>

66
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,956
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let's see if we can
find another way.</font>

67
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:03,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you have in mind?</font>

68
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:05,237
<font color="#FFFFFF">What if my claim
was acknowledged,</font>

69
00:06:05,319 --> 00:06:06,800
<font color="#FFFFFF">but I was willing
to lease the land</font>

70
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">back to the King
during his lifetime?</font>

71
00:06:08,959 --> 00:06:11,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">Or what if we deferred
judgment on ownership,</font>

72
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,598
<font color="#FFFFFF">but shared the mineral rights?</font>

73
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:17,552
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you say?</font>

74
00:06:17,639 --> 00:06:19,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">Can we start negotiating
in this manner?</font>

75
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why not?</font>

76
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have not been
given the authority to</font>

77
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,678
<font color="#FFFFFF">negotiate in this manner.</font>

78
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:36,798
<font color="#FFFFFF">You mean King Horik sent you
here with nothing but a demand?</font>

79
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:40,072
<font color="#FFFFFF">And yet he speaks of peace!</font>

80
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know
what is in his mind.</font>

81
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,151
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, then,
maybe you should ask him.</font>

82
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let me make a suggestion.</font>

83
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:54,074
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why don't you send
one of your men back</font>

84
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:57,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">so he can put to King Horik
my ideas for a remedy?</font>

85
00:06:57,319 --> 00:06:58,834
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you think that will work.</font>

86
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good. Your messenger
will take several days.</font>

87
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,836
<font color="#FFFFFF">So, in the meantime,
why don't you and</font>

88
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">your men go and visit
our famous ash tree?</font>

89
00:07:06,199 --> 00:07:07,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">It is famous not
only for its size,</font>

90
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">but because it
never loses its leaves,</font>

91
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,915
<font color="#FFFFFF">summer or winter.</font>

92
00:07:11,959 --> 00:07:14,428
<font color="#FFFFFF">Some people even
say it's Yggdrasil,</font>

93
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:16,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">the tree that holds up the sky.</font>

94
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,911
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I will
provide you an escort.</font>

95
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,031
<font color="#FFFFFF">I only have one
very small request.</font>

96
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,031
<font color="#FFFFFF">I would like one
of your men to stay</font>

97
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">behind here as
a kind of security.</font>

98
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:26,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">You understand, I hope?</font>

99
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">My brother Rollo
will stay behind.</font>

100
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,553
<font color="#FFFFFF">Floki!</font>

101
00:07:56,959 --> 00:07:58,598
<font color="#FFFFFF">So how long must we travel?</font>

102
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:01,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">It can take us three
days to reach the tree.</font>

103
00:08:04,639 --> 00:08:06,392
<font color="#FFFFFF">It looks like rain.</font>

104
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,040
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come.</font>

105
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why have you come?</font>

106
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:27,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am frightened for my husband.</font>

107
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:31,031
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you think your husband
is in some kind of danger?</font>

108
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:35,716
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've had strange
and disturbing dreams.</font>

109
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:38,476
<font color="#FFFFFF">What happens in your dreams?</font>

110
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dark shapes come to me at night.</font>

111
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,033
<font color="#FFFFFF">Monstrous forms.</font>

112
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">When I wake,</font>

113
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,671
<font color="#FFFFFF">they skulk in the
shadows, shapeless,</font>

114
00:08:48,759 --> 00:08:52,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">but no sooner am I asleep
than they creep forward again.</font>

115
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ah, yes.</font>

116
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,433
<font color="#FFFFFF">The shadows come
from Hel's hall.</font>

117
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one can ensnare them,
not even the gods.</font>

118
00:09:02,519 --> 00:09:04,476
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is it that they want?</font>

119
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">To take something from you.</font>

120
00:09:08,679 --> 00:09:09,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">My life?</font>

121
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:13,749
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, something far more
important to you than that.</font>

122
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">My husband's life?</font>

123
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:21,279
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell me.</font>

124
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,828
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why must you all force me up</font>

125
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:26,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">and unearth me to sorrows?</font>

126
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your husband is in danger,</font>

127
00:09:30,559 --> 00:09:32,677
<font color="#FFFFFF">but not for his life.</font>

128
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:36,153
<font color="#FFFFFF">He is in danger
from the magical world.</font>

129
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">How?</font>

130
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">Answer me.</font>

131
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:47,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was unwilling to speak
and I will say no more now!</font>

132
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,956
<font color="#FFFFFF">So, Rollo,</font>

133
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:09,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">how do you get on
with your brother?</font>

134
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:13,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">We get along fine.</font>

135
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:15,678
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why shouldn't we?</font>

136
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,274
<font color="#FFFFFF">No reason.</font>

137
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,431
<font color="#FFFFFF">But not all brothers
get on so well.</font>

138
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:23,080
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know that from
personal experience.</font>

139
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you mean?</font>

140
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,876
<font color="#FFFFFF">I, too, had a brother.</font>

141
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,678
<font color="#FFFFFF">I loved him.</font>

142
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:34,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">We were very close,
as befits blood brothers.</font>

143
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,558
<font color="#FFFFFF">We fought together
in the shield-wall.</font>

144
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:38,359
<font color="#FFFFFF">We shared the same women.</font>

145
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">When my father was
killed, there was</font>

146
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:44,552
<font color="#FFFFFF">fierce competition to
replace him as Jarl.</font>

147
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:46,393
<font color="#FFFFFF">And although I
was his eldest son,</font>

148
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was not sure I
was going to succeed.</font>

149
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:51,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">However, I was elected
at the thing.</font>

150
00:10:51,679 --> 00:10:53,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">We had a feast to celebrate.</font>

151
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,552
<font color="#FFFFFF">My wife was there.</font>

152
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:58,357
<font color="#FFFFFF">My young, beautiful wife.</font>

153
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,679
<font color="#FFFFFF">We'd just gotten married.</font>

154
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">And all the others who had
stood for election against me.</font>

155
00:11:07,759 --> 00:11:09,831
<font color="#FFFFFF">My brother poisoned them</font>

156
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">all.</font>

157
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,677
<font color="#FFFFFF">I only survived because</font>

158
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,510
<font color="#FFFFFF">my wife took the cup
I was about to drink from</font>

159
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,909
<font color="#FFFFFF">and drained it herself
in celebration.</font>

160
00:11:24,039 --> 00:11:26,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will never forget her screams.</font>

161
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,511
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's my wife's screams that will</font>

162
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:31,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">haunt me for
the rest of my life.</font>

163
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:39,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">My brother denied responsibility,
but his guilt was too obvious.</font>

164
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:42,552
<font color="#FFFFFF">So I blinded him
with my own hands,</font>

165
00:11:42,679 --> 00:11:45,433
<font color="#FFFFFF">and then I burned him alive.</font>

166
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,716
<font color="#FFFFFF">Although he laughed
while he was burning.</font>

167
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:58,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's what I know about
the love between brothers.</font>

168
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:05,392
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ragnar would
never do such a thing.</font>

169
00:12:06,159 --> 00:12:07,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Of course not.</font>

170
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, your brother is different.</font>

171
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your brother's a great man,</font>

172
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,116
<font color="#FFFFFF">a great warrior.</font>

173
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:19,798
<font color="#FFFFFF">As am I.</font>

174
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sure you are.</font>

175
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:27,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">And yet I've never heard of you.</font>

176
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,080
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whoa.</font>

177
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:42,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our camp is set up over here.</font>

178
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:45,274
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's some excellent fishing
upstream, under the waterfall.</font>

179
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will go.</font>

180
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,111
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I also,</font>

181
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">for everybody knows...</font>

182
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,152
<font color="#FFFFFF">Three eyes are better than one.</font>

183
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:37,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">You! Look away!</font>

184
00:13:38,159 --> 00:13:39,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who are you? Look away at once!</font>

185
00:13:41,759 --> 00:13:43,399
<font color="#FFFFFF">What are we supposed
to be looking at?</font>

186
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm blind! See? I
can't see anything!</font>

187
00:13:51,879 --> 00:13:53,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">Arne!</font>

188
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,998
<font color="#FFFFFF">What? You're going
to try to kill us</font>

189
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,720
<font color="#FFFFFF">for protecting the
reputation of our mistress?</font>

190
00:13:57,799 --> 00:13:58,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">Shame on you!</font>

191
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,548
<font color="#FFFFFF">We came upon your
mistress by chance.</font>

192
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,399
<font color="#FFFFFF">We are strangers here,</font>

193
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:07,234
<font color="#FFFFFF">traveling to the great ash
tree, guests of Jarl Borg.</font>

194
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:10,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jarl Borg? Then why didn't
you say so at once?</font>

195
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:13,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">We will just return
to our horses then.</font>

196
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:19,953
<font color="#FFFFFF">You spied on me.</font>

197
00:14:24,919 --> 00:14:26,513
<font color="#FFFFFF">We meant no harm.</font>

198
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,956
<font color="#FFFFFF">They say they are
guests of Jarl Borg.</font>

199
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you alone?</font>

200
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:35,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">We are traveling with
Earl Ragnar Lothbrok.</font>

201
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:41,509
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then I think Earl Ragnar owes
me an apology on your behalf.</font>

202
00:14:42,559 --> 00:14:43,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't you?</font>

203
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:50,231
<font color="#FFFFFF">I never knew that</font>

204
00:14:50,879 --> 00:14:53,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">fresh fish was
also packed in salt.</font>

205
00:14:55,799 --> 00:14:57,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen, it's not our fault.</font>

206
00:14:58,039 --> 00:15:00,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">We just saw her bathing.
What were we supposed to do?</font>

207
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,035
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fish.</font>

208
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">You did not see her, Ragnar.</font>

209
00:15:05,799 --> 00:15:07,677
<font color="#FFFFFF">So you get your cheek slashed,</font>

210
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">and now I'm supposed
